{
  "texts": [
    "Alternatively, data can be provided using publicly available Git repositories such as GitHub or Gitlab, but these do not offer DOIs.",
    "To both make use of user-friendly git environments and receive a DOI, a mixed solution is a possible way forward: version management can be done through GitHub, while Zenodo stores versioned and frequently updated data sets.",
    "Conveniently, some platforms like GitHub allow a repository to be linked with Zenodo semi-automatically.",
    "GitHub is then used to handle the versioning and creation of releases.",
    "At the same time, Zenodo provides the user with a DOI, making the repository findable in the Zenodo search engine (see 3)."
  ]
}